CatDescriptText: Miss Carrie Rose, 303 Jacksonia Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 9, 1957, pg. 2 with question: "Do you believe that licensed taverns are as harmful to a neighborhood as speakeasies and gambling joints? Why?" answer reads: "No, because they are legalized and people have to have a place to go.  The other places are not legal."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Carrie Rose, wearing striped shirt, light colored cardigan with paisley trim and collar, circular earrings, and dark leather coat with knitted sleeves and collar, standing in front of exterior brick wall with two windows
